df = df.sort_values(by='state')

df['city_name'] = df['city'] + ', ' + df['state']

fig = px.scatter(df, x='longitude', y='latitude', color='state',
                 hover_data=['city_name'], width=1500, height=1100)
fig.show()

you can zoom in with the functions on the top right :)

this is the finished map.

by double-clicking a state on the right, only one state may be selected, eg maine

or a multitude of states, eg new england (ct, me, ma, nh, ri, vt)
